title: Hurricane Melissa Wreaks Havoc In Jamaica | 10 News+
description: Hurricane Melissa has slammed Jamaica, wreaking havoc on the Caribbean island nation, leaving half a million people without power. title: Hurricane Melissa Heads For Cuba After Wreaking Havoc In Jamaica | 10 News+
description: Cuba is bracing for the impact of Hurricane Melissa, after the category 5 storm slammed into Jamaica, where half a million people have been left without power. Meteorologist Anne-Claire Fontan has called it the “storm of the century” for Jamaica, which experienced 300km/hr winds, widespread flash flooding, and the collapse of crucial facilities, including major hospitals. title: Nine Queensland High Schools Taught Wrong Topic For Ancient History Exam | 10 News+
description: Queensland’s curriculum authority has been put on notice by the state’s Education Minister, as the number of high schools involved in a major teaching blunder has risen to nine. 140 Ancient History students across the state were taught about the Ancient Roman Emperor Augustus Caesar, instead of his grand-uncle and predecessor Julius Caesar. title: Category 3 Hurricane Melissa Leaves Trail of Destruction Across Cuba’s Southeast | 10 News
description: Severe flash flooding is being reported in Cuba tonight, after the country’s southeast took a direct hit from the eye of Hurricane Melissa.  These are the latest pictures from Cuba’s second-largest city — released by the state-run broadcaster.  Melissa made landfall as a Category 3 storm, packing winds of up to 193 kilometres an hour. It comes after the hurricane tore through Jamaica, where a state of disaster has now been declared. title: $7.9 Billion Medicare Bulk Billing Overhaul To Take Effect In November | 10 News+
description: Australians will enjoy cheaper visits to the doctor starting November 1, when a multibillion-dollar overhaul of the Medicare bulk billing system comes into effect. GP clinics will be offered more financial incentives if they provide free appointments to any Medicare card holder. For women, the federal government scheme also includes larger rebates for menopause health assessments and long-term contraceptives. title: Jamaica Declared Disaster Zone As Hurricane Melissa Rips Through Cuba | 10 News
description: The devastation of Hurricane Melissa on Jamaica has become clearer, as the nation is declared as a disaster zone while the storm moves on to Cuba.  Melissa has been declared Jamaica's strongest ever storm on record, with four people confirmed dead in the country, while dozens have been killed in Haiti.  Eyewitness accounts show the flooding in Cuba's Holguin Province following Melissa's passage through the region.  Hundreds of Cuban rural communities have been isolated, while the city of Santiago was also heavily hit. title: Helicopter Crashes Near Everest Base Camp | 10 News
description: A private helicopter sent to rescue stranded trekkers crashed while attempting to land at Lobuche near Everest Base Camp on Wednesday.  Officials said the aircraft slipped on snow during landing and came to rest on its side.  The pilot survived and was later rescued; it is unknown whether the trekkers have been rescued.  The crash came as heavy snow and cyclone winds forced authorities to close both the Nepali and Chinese sides of the Everest region to trekkers.  Trekking routes across Annapurna, Manaslu and Dhaulagiri have also been halted amid days of severe weather and dangerous trail conditions. title: Israel Defies Ceasefire, Air Strikes Kill Over 100 In Gaza | 10 News
description: More than 100 Palestinians including 46 children have been killed in a wave of Israeli strikes in Gaza on Tuesday night.  The Israeli military said it “resumed the ceasefire” after striking "dozens of terror targets and terrorists" in response to violations by Hamas of the US-brokered ceasefire deal.  The United Nations' human rights office described the Israeli airstrikes on Gaza as “appalling” and called on all parties to implement the ceasefire. title: NASA Supersonic Plane Takes First Historic Test Flight | 10 News
description: One of the few downsides of living in Australia is the long travel times when flying internationally, but those lengthy flights could become a thing of the past. title: The Fragile Fortress: Is Australia Ready For War? | FULL DOCUMENTARY
description: It is Australia's dilemma: That the nation that buys a third of all our exports, our resources, our agricultural products, our services, whose students fill our universities, the nation that is now our second-largest source of new immigrants; this nation is also the most likely source of our next major conflict.  Hugh Riminton explores how prepared Australia really is to be drawn into a war with China involved, and how ready we are to defend our place in the world - once thought of as an island fortress - with so much at stake.
